  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: e9620f8c34305754d8cc9a7e49e852d9, type: 3}
  m_Name: Tutorial_en
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_LocaleId:
    m_Code: en
  m_SharedData: {fileID: 11400000, guid: e00198e87a257ff41b02cc989c3a409a, type: 2}
  m_Metadata:
    m_Items:
    - rid: 2319839819189715041
  m_TableData:
  - m_Id: 11264212992
    m_Localized: Hello! Welcome to Pantory!
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
      - rid: 2319839819189715041
  - m_Id: 438890283008
    m_Localized: Pantory is a factory management simulation game.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 575934971904
    m_Localized: First, let me explain how to play the game. You can view the tutorial
      at any time by clicking the question mark button in each window.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1678642659328
    m_Localized: You can see where your capital is going with the Credits and Research
      Points buttons in the top left.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2291514359808
    m_Localized: This container displays the employment status, allocation status,
      and satisfaction level of employees.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2320476028928
    m_Localized: This container has the clock, time adjustment, tutorial, and settings
      buttons.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2777508364288
    m_Localized: This is where the buttons for quickly switching between each important
      panel are located.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5943566155776
    m_Localized: Now let's talk about threads. It's easy to think of threads as a
      collection of factories.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 7203816095744
    m_Localized: When you create a thread, it uses the resources assigned to it and
      produces new resources.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 7579063697408
    m_Localized: You can install threads from this panel. Create a thread, select
      it, then place it.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 7894026567680
    m_Localized: When creating a thread, you can also set a category for the thread.
      The thread will be classified according to that category, and you can filter
      the thread categories in this panel.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 8131256401920
    m_Localized: Resources are crucial, as your primary goal is to generate them
      and sell them on the market. You can check your current resource status on
      this panel.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 9056704413696
    m_Localized: This concludes the main panel description for Pantory. There are
      tutorials for other panels, so familiarizing yourself with them will help you
      enjoy the game. We hope you enjoy your time in Pantory! Thank you!
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 11779361357824
    m_Localized: This button toggles between thread build mode and thread remove
      mode.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12960301203456
    m_Localized: This is the storage panel. This panel shows you the inventory of
      resources you currently have.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 13340426780672
    m_Localized: Resources have categories corresponding to each resource, and you
      can filter resources by category in the resource panel.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 17836750028800
    m_Localized: This is the order panel. Each group requests resources from you,
      and you accept the requests and submit the resources.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 17928651423744
    m_Localized: Each order comes from the Market, Company, and Government, and the
      size of the order tends to increase in that order. The size of the order may
      also vary depending on your company's Wealth.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18539786682368
    m_Localized: You can filter where each order came from here.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18834268766208
    m_Localized: If you accept an order, you can view the accepted orders through
      this toggle.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 19061579071488
    m_Localized: A list of clients by client category can be found here. Clicking
      on a client will display a list of orders available to that client.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 19397370855424
    m_Localized: New orders appear here. Click to accept an order and it will move
      to your accepted orders list.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 19716532224000
    m_Localized: This is the Market panel. Here you can buy and sell resources and
      view information about competing companies.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 22018345287680
    m_Localized: Here you can choose whether to display the resource view or the
      trader (competitor) view via the button.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 22020337582080
    m_Localized: This is the Resource View. You can adjust your current resource
      purchase and sale volume here.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 24215317528576
    m_Localized: Resource information is displayed here.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 24483870425088
    m_Localized: The price history of resources is visually displayed here.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 24698149027840
    m_Localized: This is the Trader (Competitor) View. You can view information about
      each trader.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 36510642880512
    m_Localized: This is the panel where you can manage your employees.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 36904429305856
    m_Localized: This shows your current management capacity. A certain number of
      managers are required per employee. If you are short on managers, employee
      satisfaction will be penalized.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 37440536854528
    m_Localized: Employee satisfaction is affected by many factors. You can see what
      is affecting it here.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 37828904239104
    m_Localized: Employee efficiency depends on their satisfaction, and this efficiency
      affects the productivity of the thread. Employees' demands also change depending
      on their satisfaction.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 38302378246144
    m_Localized: The easiest way to raise employee satisfaction is to pay them more.
      Lower pay will reduce it.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 39086448852992
    m_Localized: Employees are divided into Workers, Technicians, Researchers, and
      Managers. Workers perform simple tasks within a thread, Technicians perform
      technical tasks within a thread, Researchers produce RP (Research Points),
      and Managers are responsible for managing employees.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 39688935456768
    m_Localized: Here, you can decide whether to hire or fire employees. Hiring or
      firing employees costs credits, and firing employees will decrease their satisfaction.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2561770013474816
    m_Localized: This is the research panel. You can unlock buildings and boost productivity.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2562082698838016
    m_Localized: This is where you can see your Research Points (RP) and how many
      Research Points you gain each day.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2562316594200576
    m_Localized: This is a panel where you can see the number of researchers and
      the effects they are receiving.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2562738453102592
    m_Localized: This is the research tree. Completed research is highlighted, and
      the next connected research becomes available to unlock.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2563160425250816
    m_Localized: This is the Finance panel, where you can view your company's growth
      over time.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2564533472608256
    m_Localized: Shows your current monthly growth rate.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2565297930649600
    m_Localized: Shows your current monthly profit.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2566859943985152
    m_Localized: Shows your current company value in a graph.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2566981499109376
    m_Localized: Shows your current credits in a graph.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2568369331388416
    m_Localized: Hello. This is the design screen. Here, you can design your own
      threads.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2568866050228224
    m_Localized: This is where you can control the overall thread. There are buttons
      for resetting, saving, and loading threads.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2569802302767104
    m_Localized: Each building has a category. Production buildings have a Production
      category, and distribution buildings have a Distribution category.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2571217918115840
    m_Localized: After clicking the category button, the buttons for accessing each
      building are displayed here. Clicking a button allows you to select it and
      add it directly to your thread design.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2571541005352960
    m_Localized: Here you can change the installation direction of the selected building
      and manage the construction mode and removal mode status.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2572921984139264
    m_Localized: In design, the "road" is crucial. The efficiency of the threads
      depends on the design of the road.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2572931048030208
    m_Localized: When you install a building, there are inputs and outputs, and those
      must be aligned with the road.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2575685451661312
    m_Localized: Each input must be connected to another building's output or to
      an unloading station.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2575868566585344
    m_Localized: Connect the output to the trading office to complete the thread.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
